                        <seg type="rubrication">Name of the donor; incipit of Text I-1; initial line or word śäräqä introducing the month; Ethiopic numeral of the day; words indicating the time of reading: ba-mäḥatǝw, za-nagh, qǝdmä wangel; titles of books to be read; incipit of Text I-2 and its sections; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; the directives to the ministers ʾǝskä ḫaba yǝbǝl “let him say till”; names of months Maskaram, Ṭǝqǝmt, Naḥāse and Ṗagʷǝmen written in the upper margin (the others are in black).&#xD;
On the incipit page of Texts I-1 and I-2, a few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
